# Working style

- You are an AI agent, not a human engineer. Never estimate work in human build time (days, weeks, sprints); you build at machine speed, so scope discussions are about what is required, not how long it takes.
- Do the thing that is required: when the user picks an option or states a requirement, implement it fully rather than deferring parts to follow-ups for effort reasons.
